			Identity Hardening & cloud armor

##Objective
To build a production-grade secure web enviroment where the server is completly
hidden from the public but accessabe via a controlled, inspected gateway 

##Key concepts 

-Private VPC & Cloud NAT
A network with no external "front door." Cloud NAT acts as a 
one-way mirror, letting the VM reach out for updates without letting the 
internet see in.

-IAP (Identity-Aware Proxy)
A secure tunnel that verifies your Google Identity before allowing an SSH 
connection, removing the need for a public IP or a "jump box."

-Global Load Balancer
The official "Front Gate." It provides a single public IP that 
manages traffic and distributes it to your private backend instances.

-Cloud Armor (WAF)
A digital shield sitting on the Load Balancer that inspects every 
request for malicious code (like SQL injection) and blocks it at the edge.

